Philippine Equity Movers: Philippine Long Distance, Petroenergy

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-06-29T04:40:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/san-miguel-shang-vista-land-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 40.64, or 1
percent, to 4,249.35.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  , the
nation’s largest phone company, dropped 3.2 percent to 2,324
pesos, the steepest loss since June 16. The  Supreme Court 
directed the Securities and Exchange Commission to investigate
PLDT for a possible violation of the constitutional limit on
foreign ownership, ABS-CBN reported, without saying where it got
the information.  PLDT declined to comment on the decision as the company
hasn’t received the ruling, Ray Espinosa, head of regulatory
affairs, said in a mobile-phone message in response to questions
from Bloomberg News.  Petroenergy Resources Corp. (PERC)  , a developer and
explorer of oil and gas fields, jumped 11 percent to 6.70 pesos,
the largest increase since December 2009. Crude oil for August
delivery rose 2.5 percent yesterday, the biggest advance in
almost six weeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
